  "body": "**What is the current behavior?**\r\n\r\nUsing Prompt in a component does prevent navigation over the browser's navigation buttons in Safari, iOS 12. \r\n\r\n**Steps to reproduce**\r\n\r\nCreate a simple React app with only a home component. Place following code in the JSX file:\r\n\r\n```import React, { Component, Fragment } from 'react';\r\nimport { Prompt } from 'react-router';\r\n\r\nclass Home extends Component {\r\n   render() {\r\n      return (\r\n         <Fragment>\r\n            <h1>Prompt Test</h1>\r\n            <Prompt\r\n               when={true}\r\n               message=\"Really navigate away?\"/>\r\n         </Fragment>\r\n      );\r\n   }\r\n}\r\n\r\nexport default Home;\r\n```\r\n\r\nRun the app, goto google,com, goto the app website, tap the browser's back button.\r\n\r\n**Expected behavior?**\r\n\r\nThe browser should go back to google,com.\r\n\r\n**Current behavior**\r\n\r\nThe browser does stay on the app website.\r\n\r\n**Which versions of React, and which browser / OS are affected by this issue? Did this work in previous versions of React?**\r\n\r\nReact 16.8.1.\r\nOS: iOS 12\r\n\r\n",
